{"version":1,"entries":{"person_2029011_translations":{"at":1774698738680,"data":{"id":2029011,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"王成思，10月10日出生于山西省，中国内地影视演员，话剧演员，开心麻花舞台剧签约艺人，功勋演员。毕业于北京电影学院 。\n\n2005年王成思出演电视剧《生死相随》饰演詹如松一角  。 2006年出演开心麻花话剧《疯狂的石头》。2015年出演开心麻花话剧《牢友记》； 同年9月30日，参与喜剧电影《夏洛特烦恼》上映，饰演思思。2017年9月30日参演电影《羞羞的铁拳》上映，饰演“秀念”师兄。2018年2月16日参演《唐人街探案2》上映，饰演“对眼”打手 。","name":"王成思","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Wang Chengsi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"Wang Chengsi","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"왕성사","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"王成思，10 月 10 日出生於山西省，中國內地影視演員，話劇演員，開心麻花舞台劇簽約藝人，功勳演員。畢業於北京電影學院 。\n\n2005 年王成思出演電視劇《生死相隨》飾演詹如松一角 。\n\n2006 年出演開心麻花話劇《瘋狂的石頭》。2015 年出演開心麻花話劇《牢友記》； 同年 9 月 30 日，參與喜劇電影《夏洛特煩惱》上映，飾演思思。2017 年 9 月 30 日參演電影《羞羞的鐵拳》上映，飾演“秀念”師兄。2018 年 2 月 16 日參演《唐人街探案 2》上映，飾演“對眼”打手 。","name":"王成思","primary":false}}]}},"person_22111_translations":{"at":1774698752148,"data":{"id":22111,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"The middle of five children. His father was a police officer/detective and his mother was a social worker. He received his B.A. from St. Vincent College in Latrobe, Pennsylvania and pursued his M.F.A. on a full scholarship at the Catholic University of America in Washington, D.C. Kelly has appeared in numerous off-Broadway and off-off-Broadway productions, primarily at the Public Theater and the Second Stage. A product of regional national theater, he has been a company member of the Williamstown Theatre Festival, the Folger Theater, Arena Stage, and the Actors Theater of Louisville among others. He toured with the National Players, the oldest classical touring company in the United States. He starred on Broadway as Brick opposite Kathleen Turner in \"Cat on a Hot Tin Roof\", and as Paul Verrall opposite Madeline Kahn in \"Born Yesterday\". In 2003, he appeared at the Mark Taper Theater Forum, originating the role of Richard in \"Living Out\" by Lisa Loomer.","name":"Daniel Hugh Kelly","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"丹尼尔·休·凯利","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"丹尼爾·休·凱利","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"ダニエル・ヒュー・ケリー","primary":false}}]}},"tv_313298_credits":{"at":1774698753088,"data":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":192,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Morgan Freeman","original_name":"Morgan Freeman","popularity":11.3433,"profile_path":"/jPsLqiYGSofU4s6BjrxnefMfabb.jpg","character":"Self - Narrator (voice)","credit_id":"6984b6cac0f61b819c6e77a0","order":0}],"crew":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":488,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Steven Spielberg","original_name":"Steven Spielberg","popularity":7.5879,"profile_path":"/tZxcg19YQ3e8fJ0pOs7hjlnmmr6.jpg","credit_id":"6984b84fab2a6b236674ae66","department":"Production","job":"Executive Producer"},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":67589,"known_for_department":"Directing","name":"Alastair Fothergill","original_name":"Alastair Fothergill","popularity":0.4687,"profile_path":"/l2fqoPIjMxVLRgb8BU9AwCrDJJA.jpg","credit_id":"6984b99555a3a69f569d1bc4","department":"Production","job":"Executive Producer"},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":227452,"known_for_department":"Production","name":"Keith Scholey","original_name":"Keith Scholey","popularity":0.5664,"profile_path":"/w4Nq22lNHSegSDZK5yf